Draft the “RISK FACTORS” section of an IPO prospectus based strictly on the evidence provided below.

REQUIRED STRUCTURE

Title:
RISK FACTORS

Introductory paragraph:
- One paragraph explaining that an investment involves risks beyond the Group’s control and that these risks may materially and adversely affect the Group’s business, financial condition, results of operations and prospects.

Main Sections (use these headings exactly):
9.1 Risks Relating to Our Business and Operations

For each risk factor:
- Risk heading:
  - Must be a full sentence.
  - Must begin with “We”, “Our Group”, or “Our business”.
- Risk disclosure paragraph(s):
  - 1–2 paragraphs per risk.
  - Each paragraph may be long and legally worded.
  - Clearly describe:
    (i) the source of the risk,
    (ii) the factual background as disclosed, and
    (iii) why this creates uncertainty.
  - Conclude with an adverse impact statement such as:
    “This may materially and adversely affect our business, financial performance and prospects.”

- Cross-references:
  - Where applicable, include references such as:
    “Please refer to Section X of this Prospectus.”

Do NOT include summaries, conclusions, or mitigation statements.

